##017_Prize_rev20260307.py

##Rule 017_Prize_rev20260307.py
###08.05.2022### A fost transformata Priza4 pentru laptop
###Windows cmd pentru verificare nivel baterie: WMIC PATH Win32_Battery Get EstimatedChargeRemaining
#
# Changes vs 017_Prize_rev20260208:
#
#   BUGS FIXED:
#   - ctrl_dev defined twice. First definition used self.SEND_COMMAND (NameError).
#     Second (correct) definition silently overwrote the first. All code between
#     the two definitions called the broken version. Fixed: single correct
#     ctrl_dev at module level, used throughout.
#   - led_adina_intens = ir.getItem(...) at module load time caused NameError if
#     item registry not ready. Removed — it was unused after the lightstrip
#     functions were refactored to call ctrl_dev directly.
#   - priza1_Current TelePeriod block read Priza2_Current to set Priza1_TelePeriod
#     (copy-paste bug). Fixed: now reads Priza1_Current as intended.
#   - taperStartTime used time.time() which resets on script reload mid-charge.
#     Fixed: replaced with DateTime.now() stored as Joda DateTime object,
#     survives the same session (script reload still resets it, but that is
#     unavoidable without persistent item storage; at least the type is correct).
#   - Two rules both named "Logic Lightstrip when Sonoffmini1 turns off" /
#     "Logic Lightstrip when Sonoffmini2 turns off" — second silently overwrote
#     first in rule registry. Fixed: renamed to unique names.
#   - time.sleep(10) in logic_lightstrip_dormp_off and time.sleep(2) in
#     logic_lightstrip_sufragerie_on, logic_lightstrip_dormc_on block the rule
#     engine thread. Replaced with ScriptExecution.createTimer(..., 10s / 2s).
#
#   NEW:
#   - Priza1_BatteryFull set to ON when full-charge (trickle) detected.
#     This flag is read by 080_Power to skip Priza1 in the ECO ON-sequence.
#     Flag is reset by 019_Charge_curve when Priza1_Power turns ON, and at
#     midnight by 020_Scheduled (end of day).
#   - Priza4_BatteryFull: same pattern — reset when Priza4_Power turns ON (019_Charge_curve);
#     DelayTimer4 cancelled here so timer4_charge_off cannot fire after a manual/ECO power-on.
#     Leaving the trickle band debounces clearing Priza4_BatteryFull (see PRIZA4_LEAVE_DEBOUNCE_SEC).
#   - Priza1: relay max uses MaxCLevel_P1_Night for night/bed when that value is > MinCLevel_P1_1;
#     taper window no longer opens relays as “below min”; DelayTimer1 now created (timeoutMinutesP1);
#     taper/full end cancels that timer.
#   CONVENTION 2026-05-02: UnDefType already org.eclipse.smarthome.core.types (ESH; OH 2.5.12).
#     Project rule: prefer ESH over org.openhab.core.* for core types — see 000_utils header.
#   2026-05-23 FIX-D: Removed unused imports 'from threading import Timer' and
#     'from core.actions import Exec' — neither was referenced anywhere in the file.
#   2026-05-23 FIX-E: MaxCLevel_P1_Night (0.095 A) < MinCLevel_P1_1 (0.300 A) so
#     priza1_relay_max_current() night branch is always False — documented in-place.
#   2026-05-23 FIX-F: timer1_charge_off now sets _p1_timer_relay_open flag so that the
#     current→0 reading after relays open skips BatteryFull detection (not a genuine full
#     charge — just a timeout relay-open). Flag cleared in priza1_Current.
#   2026-05-23 FIX-G: Removed redundant 'if auto != OFF:' guard inside 'if auto == ON:'
#     block in priza1_control — it was always True and never needed.

